UMAP & HDBSCAN Rational Workflow

Simon Coetzee
2020-06-12

Clustering in High Dimentions

Four main options:

  • Hierarchical clustering
    • sensitive to noise
  • Centroid-based clustering
    • spherical or ellipsoid symmetry
  • Graph-based clustering
    • number of clusters has to be assigned a-priori
  • Density-based clustering
    • clustering without specifying the number of clusters
    • cluster shape independent

Clustering Examples

Initialization of UMAP

By default uses Laplacian eigenmaps.

It builds a graph from knn in high dimentions.

Very high dimentionality causes some trouble for euclidean distance.

Replace full dimentionality of binary data with lower dimentionality of MCA.

Multiple Correspondence Analysis

Represents data as points in low dimentional euclidean space.

The counterpart of PCA for categorical data.

Multiple Correspondence Analysis - Optimizing Dimentionality

mca_res <- MCA(X = gdc_path_mca_nolab, graph = FALSE)
expl_var <- mca_res$eig[,2]
barplot(mca_res$eig[,2][1:50], 
        ylab = "explained variance", 
        names.arg = paste0("MCA", 1:50), col = "darkgreen")

Multiple Correspondence Analysis - Optimizing Dimentionality

N_perm <- 100
expl_var_perm <- matrix(NA, ncol = length(mca_res$eig[,2]), nrow = N_perm)
for(k in seq(N_perm)) {
  gdc_perm <- as.data.frame(lapply(gdc_path_mca_nolab, sample))
  MCA_perm <- MCA(X = gdc_perm, graph = FALSE)
  expl_var_perm[k,] <- MCA_perm$eig[,2]
  print(paste0("FINISHED ",k," PERMUTATIONS"))
}

Multiple Correspondence Analysis - Optimizing Dimentionality

plot(expl_var[1:50]~seq(1:50),ylab="EXPLAINED VARIANCE",main="VARIANCE EXPLAINED BY MCA",
     col="darkgreen",type='o',xlab="MCA Dimentions")
lines(colMeans(expl_var_perm)[1:50]~seq(1:50),col="red")

Multiple Correspondence Analysis - Optimizing Dimentionality

pval <- apply(t(expl_var_perm) >= expl_var,1,sum) / N_perm
plot(pval[1:50]~seq(1:50),col="darkred",type='o',xlab="MCA Dimentions",ylab="PVALUE",
     main="SIGNIFICANCE OF MCA Dimentions")


optPC<-head(which(pval>=0.05),1)-1
mca_res <- MCA(X = gdc_path_mca_nolab, ncp = optPC, graph = FALSE)

UMAP + HDBSCAN

file_name <- "gdc_reactome_filteredpath_analysis"
optPerp <- round(sqrt(nrow(mca_res$ind$coord)),0)
N_cells <- nrow(mca_res$ind$coord)
custom.settings <- umap.defaults
custom.settings$n_neighbors <- optPerp
custom.settings$min_dist <- 1e-6
custom.settings$n_components <- 3
n_epochs <- 1000
method <- "umap-learn"
config <- custom.settings

UMAP + HDBSCAN Optimize minimum cluster size

N_iter <- 60
N_pt <- 150
score <- vector(length = N_pt - 2)

for(i in 3:N_pt) {
  print(paste0("MIN POINTS = ",i))
  score_iter <- foreach (1:N_iter, 
                         .combine = c, 
                         .export = c("mca_res", "config", "method", "n_epochs"), 
                         .packages= c("dbscan", "umap")) %dopar% 
    {
      umap_init_mca <- suppressWarnings(umap(mca_res$ind$coord, 
                                             config = config, 
                                             method = method, 
                                             n_epochs = n_epochs, 
                                             init = mca_res$ind$coord[, 1:3]))
      res <- hdbscan(umap_init_mca$layout, minPts = i)
      score_iter_temp <- sum(res$membership_prob < 0.05) / N_cells
      return(score_iter_temp)
    }
  score[i-2] <- mean(score_iter, na.rm = TRUE)
}

UMAP + HDBSCAN Optimize minimum cluster size

plot(log(score + 1) ~ seq(from=3, to=N_pt, by=1), type='o', xlab="MIN SIZE OF CLUSTERS", ylab="LOG ( SCORE )")
names(score) <- seq(from=3, to=N_pt, by=1)
opt_score <- min(as.numeric(names(score)[score==min(score)]))
mtext(paste0("OPTIMAL MIN SIZE OF CLUSTERS = ",opt_score))

UMAP + HDBSCAN Final output

set.seed(42)
cluster_layout <- umap(mca_res$ind$coord, config = config, method = method, n_epochs = n_epochs, init = mca_res$ind$coord[, 1:3])
custom.settings$min_dist <- 0.01
config <- custom.settings
umap_init_mca <- umap(mca_res$ind$coord, config = config, method = method, n_epochs = n_epochs, init = mca_res$ind$coord[, 1:3])
res_opt <- hdbscan(cluster_layout$layout, minPts = opt_score)
df_opt <- as.data.frame(umap_init_mca$layout)
df_opt$clust <- res_opt$cluster
df_opt$clust_knn_87[df_opt$clust==0] <- class::knn(umap_init_mca$layout[which(df_opt$clust!=0),],
                                                   umap_init_mca$layout[which(df_opt$clust==0),],
                                                   df_opt$clust[df_opt$clust!=0], k=87)
